# MIQ performance corpus — copy this file to `testcases.txt` (gitignored) and
# point it at real files on your machine.
#
# Format: <label><whitespace><absolute path>.  Blank lines and `#` ignored.
# The label is the stable key used to match a case against baseline.json, so
# keep it constant across releases (rename the file, not the label).
#
# Pick a representative spread: each format, 3D + 4D, compressed + not, and at
# least one large file per format so IO/decompression cost is exercised.

nii-3d    /absolute/path/to/structural.nii
nii-gz-3d /absolute/path/to/structural.nii.gz
nii-gz-4d /absolute/path/to/dwi_4d.nii.gz
mif-4d    /absolute/path/to/fod.mif
mgz-3d    /absolute/path/to/freesurfer.mgz
nrrd-3d   /absolute/path/to/scan.nrrd
